Manchester United legend, Rio Ferdinand has named Paris Saint-Germain as the favourites team to qualify for the Champions League quarter-final ahead of Real Madrid. PSG and Real Madrid will clash in the Champions League round of 16 second-leg tie in March at the Santiago Bernabeu. The French Ligue 1 giants had won Real Madrid 1-0 in the Champions League round of 16 first-leg encounter. Speaking to Canal Supporters, Ferdinand said, “I think they [PSG] are favourites! I watched the team, and the squad is crazy! With the talent and depth they have, it is really good! I think they are the favourites against Real Madrid [in the Champions League].” He added, “It’s going to be a tough game. “They showed in the last match []first-leg], if they play like that with intensity, pressing, quickly recovering the ball, for the three superstars in attack and to have an opportunity to score… Then they will win.”